The evidence with the title 'The Influenza Epidemic Of 1918 ' says World War I claimed an estimated 16 million lives. The influenza epidemic that swept the world in 1918 killed an estimated 50 million people . One fifth of the world 's population was attacked by this deadly virus. Within months  ... In late spring of 1918 , the first phase , known as the "three-day fever," appeared without warning . 
